Let me know your thoughts! Recipe:  * 4 large potatoes diced into cubes  * 1 diced onion * 2 large carrots peeled and diced * 1 pound diced ham * 2 teaspoons fresh parsley chopped * 1/2 tsp dried thyme * 1/3 tsp salt  * 1/2 tsp pepper * 4 cups broth (chicken or beef) * 1 cup heavy whipping cream  * 2tbsp cornstarch * 1/2 sour cream  * Optional: top with shredded cheese  - Place everything except for the sour cream, cornstarch, heavy whipping cream in the crock pot.  - Cover on low for 6-7 hours or on high for 3-3.5 hours until the potatoes are the tender - Then stir in the cornstarch with the heavy whipping cream. Add the mixture and the sour cream into the crock pot. Cover and cook on low for 30 minutes or on high for 15 minutes until the soup has thickened   - Fresh bread goes great with this on a cold day 🥖 #foodwaste #frugal #frugalmeals #frugallife #homemaker #homemaking #cheapmeals

videos.voice_to_text: Welcome to a day in my life as a chronically ill homemaker.
videos.video_description: This is partly a joke, partly reality. I don't spend every minute of the day on the couch. But when my health flares up and I have no energy, this is often what it looks like. I do usually manage to get dinner and do some dishes, but that's about all I can manage some days.  I made this because I know many of you can relate. I'd like to do a more realistic day in the life when I'm having a flare, but they take energy to make. So I hope this brings a little awareness that many of us housewives are chronically ill, and that's one of the reasons why we stay home. I get so many "why don't you just work" comments - first, I don't need a reason to stay home. But secondly I do have a really good reason 😅 #tradwife #chronicallyill #chronicillness

videos.voice_to_text: good morning everyone I obviously was not ready to be awake but here we are starting the day as I said before everyday is a line of hope day today we are saying their names I can't be the only one that wishes that making your bed was just as easy as snapping your fingers let's get that laundry going before the sun even comes up that's how you know you're gonna have a productive day all I have is one load to do today so in it goes just a small load but let's get it done bringing this little guy downstairs as he is my early riser and Mister Jonah turn the light on all by himself so proud of him now let's go make some coffee because my day cannot start without that much needed caffeine on to feeding the puppers I just switch their food from chicken to lamb because they're huskies so I feel like they need that extra protein and the lamb had more protein than the chicken what do you feed your dogs we used to actually cook real meals for them and then that just became really expensive when all the prices of food went up so now they're back to dog food again my water is fully purified so it's safe for them to drink here are my fur babies coffee is coming along nicely my house smells like Starbucks I love it Turbo asked to go out so here we are and then it's back inside to make breakfast for my babies today's menu is the same as yesterday for breakfast they are having apple slices Turkey bacon and cinnamon raisin bread with some frosting on top again their bread is gluten free egg free milk free tree nut peanut soy shellfish anything that you can name that's on the top eight allergen menu it's free of and surprisingly so it's really flavorful we're just gonna spread that icing on there and this is my version of a cinnamon roll since they can't have cinnamon rolls this is like the closest thing and here is their breakfast I still have two sleepers but Jonah will enjoy now let's empty the dishwasher again I wish it was that easy and it's time to make my coffee don't I look so happy about it today we're just doing black coffee with some creamer I wanted hazelnut creamer and they didn't have it so I had to settle for this vanilla caramel I'm gonna enjoy the sunrise while drinking my morning coffee and then I'm gonna get ready to prep the homeschool materials for today this coffee definitely hit the soul much needed so today we're going to be doing math science and reading and I have a special surprise for Noah and Jonah I got these awesome books and these pens on TikTok shop I'll have them linked below but as a homeschooling mom I found that handwriting with boys is definitely not the easiest so we're working on it everyday but these books have grooves in them so it should help guide their pen and they're reusable so here are their books that they're gonna be working on today and I'm gonna go enjoy the rest of my coffee I hope you have a great morning

videos.voice_to_text: alright friends here is a what my kids eat in a day video first off take a look at the meal plan for the day this is from the other day but you get the idea obviously we start with breakfast where they're having bananas waffles and Turkey sausage I'm gonna preface this with all of these items are allergy friendly for my kids between the three of them they are allergic to gluten eggs milk peanut tree nuts soy and shellfish so this is all safe for them so I get that all plated up and they eat that lunch is at 12 so I started making lunch around 11:51 and they are having little wraps Ari will have a regular cheese stick and the boys will have just vegan square cheese cut up and then apples of course Aria has salami roll UPS and Noah has Mayo with chicken Jonah does not like the roll up so he just has chicken and salami rolled up itself we use vegan Mayo of course because allergies it honestly tastes exactly like the regular thing I don't know what makes it so different except for the fact that there's no egg in it this is one of their favorite lunches I must say and with having kids with allergies it makes it really difficult to find a lot of different options that work for all of them so these wraps just work for us now I wanna get into why we've been doing this meal plan I like schedules I like structure and this has to go for food as well if it was up to my kids they would eat 24 7 because they can and being homeschooled kids they're home all day long so they have access to unlimited food which is great I want them to be able to eat but at the same time I don't want them to eat everything in one day cause it can't just be my kids that will eat a whole bag of apples in one day or is it just my kids I don't know but by making these meal plans and letting them know what time each meal is and having them know exactly what they're gonna have it really helps I keep a copy of this meal plan on the refrigerator so they know exactly what to expect all day long so they can prepare themselves of what they're having for each meal so here's their lunch they ate every single bite then around 3:40 I started getting dinner ready because dinner was at 4 this is a super easy one it's just nachos now when I say nachos you have to remember my kids are allergic to half the toppings but we do what works for us so all I do is cook meat and I season it with taco seasoning obviously and I add some cornstarch to make it a little thicker today we're using these round tortilla chips the kids really don't like them as much as the triangle one I don't know what the difference is it's just a shape but I will make sure I get the triangle ones next time but I place those on the plate and I top with some of the vegan mozzarella cheese that we have and I pop it in the microwave for like 30 seconds just to melt that cheese down real life cheese is honestly the best vegan cheese out there for melting purposes so if you need vegan cheese definitely get that I just topped it with some meat and olives and they enjoyed it and this is what my kids ate for the day they were happy their bellies were full and that's all that matters if you wanna see more videos like this just let me know in the comments what's your kid's favorite meal

videos.voice_to_text: I used to gain quite a bit, but the joy that would bring me has faded with time. And of course, being a family man of six, family necessities and other commitments do not exactly allow much time. As it is, I find myself listening to music a lot while also doom scrolling TikTok, where I come across numerous videos of your podcast. If you're doom scrolling TikTok, your 20 minutes turns into two hours real fucking quick. So prioritize a set day. Every Wednesday from 8 to 10:00. At night, you're off limits. Put your phone on do not disturb. Put the kids to bed and go do something for yourself. Go read a book, go tinker with something in the garage. Go to the gun range, go play video games if that's what makes you happy. Every Wednesday from 8 to 10:00. You not having a hobby and you not having a reason to, like, exist other than work and taking care of somebody else, you're not living. You're a servant. That's a fucking problem. It's no different than the stay at home mom that never does self care. We need that. Men need that, right?

videos.voice_to_text: it is a crappy Saturday here in Central Florida it's forecasted for scattered thunderstorms and rain all day so I decided to bring out a new toy for the kids Astro shot Gemini the perfect game for the whole family it came with everything that we needed which was the two guns all the balls and even a stand to shoot at what I loved most was there were no batteries needed so it was an easy setup and even easier that I don't need to replace batteries every time that they die I started by loading up each of the guns with the colour ball that match the gun it was super easy just to pop them in I know everybody is probably familiar with a Nerf gun which I've had a ton of them for my kids over the years but what I liked better about these guns is that the Little Bullets didn't have that plastic tip on the top it was just the Nerf ball so I didn't have to worry about the little plastic tip ever disconnecting from the bullet in this case a ball once I had all these loaded up I set it up in the playroom for the kids and they went at it here's Jonahs scoping out the situation these guns work on air pressure so when you move it back and forth the ball pops out it took Noah a bit of strength so daddy helped out Aria got five points so she was pretty excited and see Jonah was even loading the guns which was super easy so if a four year old can do it you can do it here's daddy helping Jonah cause again he need a little bit of strength for this the dogs even enjoyed it and Noah finally started getting the hang of it safe to say they were having fun I mean they tried right that's all that matters Aria was trying so hard to get a 30 and Jonah was really excited and she did get a 30 as well as a 10 so super proud of her Astro Shot was fun for all ages as you can clearly see everybody had a blast literally overall this is the perfect rainy Saturday activity ever I definitely recommend this toy for everybody

videos.voice_to_text: I just woke up and I'm at my boyfriend's house and he's asleep in the other room but I wanna answer you my relationship with my children changed after leaving my marriage because I no longer had like you say this partner that I needed to tend to like whenever we got in an argument and it was all the time it's this cycle of abuse this toxic cycle so you know we have the big blow up argument and then it's gonna take days to sort that out the feelings and everything and in those days I'm not really gonna be present with my children because I'm so distracted at the hurt and pain and confusion of what's going on in my relationship so you know I'm spending my days kind of pushing my kids away like hey yeah yeah yeah can you go do something else can you do this can you do that cause I'm trying to like hide from them and so you know I'm tryna hide my feelings from them I'm tryna hide what's going on from them cause you know you don't wanna fight in front of the kids so there's just like the whole relationship with the kids is very superficial cause I'm hiding so much from them so the minute I left I had no choice but to be authentic and vulnerable in front of them there was no longer anything to hide behind I no longer had this relationship that I was running behind closed doors to argue about I now had to like just be there and be present with my kids and it fucking paid off like I know when you're trying to hide arguing from the kids you kind of you also hide your emotions cause you don't wanna be like oh I'm crying cause Mommy and daddy got in an argument so you're just like you know constantly hiding and lying everything from your children so there's no way you're gonna have that deep of a relationship they can feel that you know I don't I don't know you know and so being able to be completely honest and vulnerable with my kids and you know they no longer could see me as this super mom I was now a total human they could see me cry they saw my weak moments they saw me when I'm like I don't know I don't know what we're gonna do but we're gonna figure it out so I think they have been able to see also how much I love them to what links I will actually go to to support them to be there for them to give them not just what they need but make it happy and fun so also like even the mundane moments in our house are no longer eggshell scattered all over the floor just our regular average shit in our house nothing special just that is healing and nice because we're not waiting for someone to come yell at us or tell us what we're doing wrong or you know so yeah literally being in a shitty relationship is going to keep a separation between you and your children and when you finally make the choice to leave and decide well I have these children that really need me and I'm gonna put them first and put myself first the relationship is literally what I dreamed of so hope that helps

A slightly more realistic one for this trend 😉 In stories we've been talking about all the videos we've been seeing recently where people are claiming they've made thousands, even hundreds of thousands from posting a simple video of them driving or drinking coffee. While that sounds wonderful, that isn't the story of most of us content creators on here.  In reality, most of us content creators who are making money are posting higher quality content that takes longer to make, trying to create valuable digital products, and in general bring value to people's lives. I think of @reallyverycrunchy for example - her social media is her livelihood, but look at the work she puts into her videos!  Anyway, as someone who has been creating content on IG for about 5 years, and who started actively putting work and time into this account one year ago, I thought this "what I made" video would be helpful for you.  If you've been wondering how to make money on instagram - I don't have a course or guide to sell you. IG does not monetize! I've only been able to bring in money via my Patreon (where I am also constantly creating valuable content), and affiliates (I made $400 this year from affiliates). So, if you want to make money online, maybe work on building up a following and then create digital products that hit your audience's pain points.  It's all about value. ❤ #tradwife #traditionalwife #contentcreator

Listen. If you’ve been following me for a while you’d know where I stand within the Trad Wife community. One of my pinned videos I go into LENGTHY detail. But in lieu of a recent article of a woman sharing her story about how she’s getting a divorce because her husband became infatuated with a content creator and started having an affair, I have to say, that kind of behavior from men is NOT WELCOME HERE. I identify as a trad wife in that I PERSONALLY find joy and fulfillment in my traditionally gendered role within the home. There is NOTHING wrong with that. What IS wrong is insisting that ALL women will find fulfillment in this role, and that is not the case! I am here to uplift ladies who are ALREADY like myself, I am not here to say everyone MUST live this way, because that’s not realistic. I am here to teach. I am here to inspire. And I am here to be a safe haven in our chaotic world. So if you are a GUY who is in want of a “trad wife” please ask yourself: why? Are you the type of man someone would want to take care of? What are your goals? Do you view marriage as a team with and agreed upon structure or as just a hierarchy of authority? And lastly and MOST importantly, the women currently in your life and the ones who have left… what are their thoughts of you? - Their answers will be the most telling and you will may need humility and meekness to learn from their answers. • • • #tradwife #tradwifetok #tradwivesoftiktok #tradwives #homemaker #homemaking #sahm

"Tradwife" is a fairly inclusive, yet exclusive term. We all look different - some of us wear prairie style clothes, some 1950s, others just modern clothes.  Some of us have children, others don't.  Some of us homestead and live in the country, and others live in the city.  Some of us rely 100% on our husband's income, some of us work!  None of these things define us as traditional wives, and really, all of that is traditional. Even working - women have been working for all of time!  I think the main thing is that as traditional wives, we seek to follow God's design for the family. We respect our husbands as the main breadwinner and the head of the home. As wives, we see our roles as the help meet - and what we do as helper to our husbands will vary from family to family. Our homes are our priority - and our families even more so. Tending to the home is primarily our role as wives, so, we prioritize that over our hobbies or jobs.  And lastly, we believe God designed men and women with completely separate sets of abilities, talents, and roles. We are not interchangeable but complimentary to one another. This often drives much of our lifestyles.  P.S. I understand that, while much of this post is true, I may not be speaking for every woman who calls herself a traditional wife. This is mainly what I believe and have observed from others in the community, but I understand that there are caveats and varying opinions. My word is not the gospel truth, so please don't think that I believe it is. ❤️ #tradwife #traditionalwife #homemaker

videos.voice_to_text: I met Connor every single day after that. Each day he brought something new to share with me. The first few times he brought donuts, and then he brought fruit or bottles of water and packets of Kool Aid. Although it might sound odd for him to bring those things, in my eyes they were the best. Having to live on rations from week to week, simple things like donuts and Kool Aid were luxury items. And we're not included in our weekly ration crates. Our weekly ration crates included flour, powdered milk, rice, oranges, Tang, potatoes, canned beans, dried peas, and a week's supply of some of the other vegetable or another. Sometimes it was broccoli or green beans. Other times it would be asparagus or carrots. It wasn't the best food, and it soon became boring to eat over and over every single week. But I couldn't complain. There were no such things as grocery stores anymore. So the usual things I like to eat, I no longer existed. I had been seeing Connor every day for over a month and my parents being questioning what I was doing every day. They didn't question my whereabouts at first because they just assumed I was a regular, bored 18 year old who needed to get out. They trusted me a lot.

videos.voice_to_text: A follower of mine in Instagram sent me a cleaning hack and I wanted to give it a try. Cleaning my oven is always a huge burden and it takes forever, but with the Pummy scouring stick it took like maybe a half an hour. This oven cleaning tip didn't use any harsh chemicals and didn't require me to use the sometimes dangerous self cleaning feature on my oven. You only need to use a very light pressure. Look just with my finger scouring stick didn't scratch my oven at all. So long as you just use water and the stick you should be good to go. I didn't get my oven one hundred percent perfect after all. I don't want it to be 100% perfect because it isn't often that I use regularly and I want it to look like I actually cook in my home. But I do have to say that I am very, very impressed by this hack. Give it a try!

videos.voice_to_text: Feel like DV has kind of spread itself really thin, and the way that people are using it and now really, anything, people just throw that label onto it. So what are some things that you would outline as being, like, true domestic violence? There is the school of thought that violence is only physical. Right? And it's not. I think over the last, you know, couple decades, do they really look at the effects of physical abuse as well as psychological abuse or financial abuse and all of those things? And. And there's a really wonderful graphic called The Power and Control Wheel. I don't know if you're familiar with it, but it. It kind of outlines the different areas that, um, someone who is perpetrating any sort of domestic violence is going to kind of take hold of the situation and hold on to the situation. And to me, that would be abuse. Any. Anything that robs you of your power in a situation where it should be equal, to me, feels like an abuse of power.

This is a bit of a controversial topic but I like to prepare when we have a guest coming over to visit.  Especially, when I know that they notice these 3 things… Stick around for the last one, it’s a true story… 1. The smell of your home Apparently, we become nose-blind to our own home smell. But when you walk into someone’s home, it’s often one of the first things that you notice as a guest.  It will either be a nice smell or one that’s not so great.  So I like to change the bins regularly and open windows to help keep my home smelling fresh. 2. Bathroom cleanliness  The bathroom is said to be the first place you should clean when expecting guests. A not so clean bathroom can be off putting for guests. Especially when it’s not theirs. Once I used someone’s loo and there wasn’t any loo roll. Luckily, I had backup! I clean mine daily and always double check it before a guest uses it because I’ve got children using it regularly. 3. Pet hair As a previous dog owner, I know pet hair can get everywhere and can also stick to your guests once they sit on your sofa.  I was once invited for dinner by someone who had a couple of dogs and my plate had several pet hairs on it. 🫣 When I had a dog, I used to vacuum more frequently to make sure the house wasn’t covered in pet hair. Have you always had a positive experience when you’ve been a guest in someone’s home? FOLLOW for more like this & SAVE for later.
